docs.lead_paragraph: The report of James G. McDonald, High Commissioner for Refugees Coming From Germany, as published here yesterday revealed the organization in the United States of a Refugee Economic Corporation, with a capital of $10,000,000. IIe stated that "at present the capital subscribed amounts to $1,250,000, of which part is being called up with a view to immediate assistance of settlement schemes."

docs.snippet: Foreign exchanges showed a moderately firm undertone last week, the general list showing advances ranging from a fraction of a cent to 5 points. The only exception to the forward trend was a softness in the guilder and belga, which declined. Business...
docs.lead_paragraph: Foreign exchanges showed a moderately firm undertone last week, the general list showing advances ranging from a fraction of a cent to 5 points. The only exception to the forward trend was a softness in the guilder and belga, which declined. Business was in good volume throughout the week.
